-- AngloGold, Kumba, Omnia, Pinnacle Could Move: South African Stocks Preview
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a   a n d   N i c k y   S m i t h
-- 2011-01-28T06:19:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-27/ucs-group-pinnacle-point-may-move-equity-market-preview-for-south-africa.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index climbed for
a second day, adding 173.30, or 0.5 percent, to 32,138.54 at the
5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG SJ): Africa’s largest producer
of the metal closed its Siguiri mine in Guinea for two days
earlier this week because of protests in the country. Shares in
the company added 3.80 rand, or 1.2 percent, to 311.95 rand.  Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.  (KIO SJ): South Africa may insist that
the Anglo American Plc unit supplies  iron ore  to Imperial Crown
Trading Ltd. under terms similar to those it had with steelmaker
ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd., Business Day reported. Shares
in Kumba gained 9.90 rand, or 2.2 percent, to 467.50 rand.    Omnia Holdings Ltd . (OMN SJ): The South African fertilizer
producer said it’s in talks about buying two blending plants
from Sasol Ltd. Omnia shares fell 57 cents, or 0.8 percent, to
74.98 rand.    Pinnacle Point Group Ltd . (PNG SJ): The resort and leisure-
development company holds a shareholders’ meeting to approve the
issue of 1.3 billion shares for a total price of 13 million rand
($1.8 million) to Trilinear Empowerment Trust. Shares in
Pinnacle were unchanged at 2 cents.    UCS Group Ltd . (UCS SJ): The computer-services company has
scheduled a shareholders’ meeting for today. UCS shares declined
5 cents, or 2.2 percent, to 2.25 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 0.4 percent to $25.07.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd . (AU US) dropped 2.1 percent to $43.72.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) fell 1.2 percent to $77.48. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) lost 3.6 percent to $4.47. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) retreated 2.5 percent to $15.96. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) slipped 1.1 percent to $10.70. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) lost 1.9 percent to $29.45. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
jumped 3.4 percent to $5.16. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) dropped 1.3
percent to $49.86.  To contact the reporter on this story:
